# claude-discord bridge — local config

# === REQUIRED ===

# Discord bot token. Generate at:
#   https://discord.com/developers/applications -> your app -> Bot -> Reset Token
BRIDGE_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=

# YOUR Discord user ID (numeric, 18-19 digits) — only this user can use the
# bridge; everyone else's DMs are silently dropped. To get it:
#   Discord -> User Settings -> Advanced -> Developer Mode (on)
#   then tap your own profile -> Copy User ID.
BRIDGE_ALLOWED_USER_ID=

# === OPTIONAL ===

# Working directory passed to `claude` (`cwd`). Defaults to your home dir.
# Claude Code resolves CLAUDE.md, hooks, and project context from here.
# BRIDGE_WORKDIR=/home/you/code/myproject

# Path to the `claude` binary. Auto-detected via `which claude` if unset.
# Override if you have multiple installs or a non-PATH location.
# BRIDGE_CLAUDE_BIN=/home/you/.local/bin/claude
